TextBlock.TextLine: & have this day opened the northrens butt the time did not permitt
to considder riew them as I should do where fore intend pr my next toyme
you a full accompt whilst itt will not be amis in case you have inorder
an other pack off Dozins as pr my last mentioned: Rich pindar
is not yett arrived I shall exspect the EE yallowmarckes as soone as
possible intrim buy IWW. red marck pack whices & dusparche them with
all speed, & in case you sppose that that sort might vise more & could
advise you to buy 10 wiro red markes, butt them you must disprch
without de laye I have once disired 2 spanish wooll bayes as last, y
R.K. with mixt. list of 90 ƒ & you send mee 4 swankins course diris
att go which are not worth a farting more then those of the green
streepken besides I have told you more often of yd bayes wrasppers
you note then constantely att 43 a 43„6 where as those I have from
the north att 36 a 37 st are much better so you must gett bayes cheaper
or send for from the north, or oathere non attall for I can not
advance up on them as sought to do, so nay amend yd hand there in
inclosed send you a remise of £116:2t on in samuel schepheard
for which pleased to procured the needfull & past to my accompt I hope
suddamly to be forward on that intending to remitt you everij week pray
present mij service to mr slaughter & tell him that m. peeters isarrhnd
att brussels & that now I hope thatt actt will be cleared sudd aruly in which
mij endeavour shall be continued till hebesatis sied & so remaine
Luoy knightley
you please to in order for mee from m'sijkes 2 packes of cloathes to be
alsorted of each pattarnes one duble peece rve
2 ofingle dosins to be made up as so whole cloathes as he did with the least
bale to be in prijses from 3:3„ to 3 6 pence ayd raw
10 broad or longcloathes of each patt. one peeces to bee from 4stat5 st ay

a lovely mixture each cloth to be some what broader foulded
as he used to do & the fine cloathes toilletted & drest pprest allthe

Londen A bram virant
S. my last to you was on the ont 30:h past with a note of rectore
lane one of the officers of akings yaght undercapt fase bie for
a packett of lace N. 44 sent a long with him, which I supose is now about
arrived I hope itt will come safe to ydn inclosed is a noted of the parik
& prijses N100 & 112 „ 114 are wee are not full agreed differing a small
matter, & I am to pay them this ewening so you shall have apersect
in voyce p next whilst att the gouy off of the post receavedyd
of 13 past. I hope the packett N.13 with you to content & that these
2 last will sett off all the rest, which now time will te ach what
new modes you shall want, in which I shall not faile to endeavar
to promite yd intrest intrim you would know what mea sures
to take in proceeding of our trade as to that I'll given you avery
excut accompt p. first you did supose that I should have ordered
a fair Ireater parcell then now I have don, by that I understand
that you mu stooke my meaning for I have sent pastaine to provive
of each sort one pack butt I want of each sort att least y pathes
so in case you leave the whold concernies to one man order him
to prande 4packes of eack 12 fine cloathes from 4:6 4o5:2
4 packes of eack 12 ditto from 3:10 to4:4
4 packes of each 24 single about 3 a 3:6 ayd raw
Butt first I tought you would have made atryall of 2 or 3 men more
& that assortment & instructions I sent you was for yo. governo that
each mun should do accordingly & that then wee should p roceed with
him that die best now seeng you supose mr. potter will do well lett
him have yd ooder as fors as 4 of packes of each sortall according
to the patt sent I have recd. N.31 butt they prove not well so wee will
leave him that, bought them & keep on toun potter & lett him
dohis endeavous & send the goods forward when ready my nextshall
given order forf kersies pray dispatch the bayes & so remaine
I hope to be aremistiny p firs for boath accompts
In Antwerpen 5 Maij 1681
Brussel Antons Peeters, compa
Mess. in antwoort aenden ul van 1 deser geirne gesien dat monsr. ul brode
van England was t huys gekomen, doch tot mijn leet wesen soo indispoose
hijen heeft geen ongelijck als hij ul blammeert ten regard van de rekening
want schoon ick ul daer selfs daer over heb geschreven, ende dat ul oock
hier in stadt heeft geweest nochtans hebbe noyt iets sedert sijn leest
vertrek vernomen ick hebbe al gedaen dat ick gekost hebbe om eenigh
goet te verkoopen, ende gelt int voorderen vant welke eenighincas sal
dsijn: tis mij leet die van londen hem souden hebben geaffronteert
en te meer omdat ul seght sulx niet soude geschiet hebben waert saken
sij £50 a 60 hadden ontfangen, had ick daer toe gversocht geweest
soude dat wel uyt gevonden, hebben, die voor meerder ben geiugageert
geweest, eghter hoe eerder ul gelieve alles te doen advisteeren, hoe lieven
ick het hebbe, sijnde tot dien eijnde gereet & seer genegen ter wijlen
In Antwerpen aij
Brugge Raphael Coots
monsr. op 2 deser is aen ul mijnen leesten, sedert geene van ull tgeene mij
continueert in goede hope, tsucces verlangende noch heden te verstaen
tot london is es voor mij geladen aen boort omert verscriek 3 packen
MN.17 met 12 spaense modecolleurs lakens
KN. 5 & 6 ider met 5 dobbel roij lakens
Aen boort Rogier vandewalle spack MN o8 met ½ & ½ spaense lakens voor
deen & dander gelieft aen arrivemente het noodich te besorgen & mij vant gepass
advies te geven terwijlen —blijve
7 maij 1681
London hemy marynard
mj last te yen was on t he 3: uittsencr non from you. then sended you

porten att ½ nso also for ney aett besiders a small fum for £29: 4: at 2 uso

hether, & hul man writ es verij dubrour about the samd. onert versiick is
